Class Word

java.lang.Object
appDomain.Word
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Word>
public class Word extends Object implements Comparable<Word>, Serializable
Represents a word stored in the BST and tracks all occurrences of that word across multiple files and line numbers.

This class is used by the word-indexing application to store:

  • The word itself
  • A mapping of filenames â†’ list of line numbers where the word appears
The class implements:
  • Comparable<Word> so it can be ordered alphabetically in the BST
  • Serializable so it can be saved to / loaded from repository.ser

      public void addOccurrences(String filename, int lineNumber)
      Adds an occurrence of the word at a given filename and line number. If the file has no previous occurrences stored, a new list is created.
      Parameters:
      filename - the file where the word was found
      lineNumber - the line number in the file

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Word other)
      Compares two Word objects alphabetically, ignoring case.

      This allows the BST to maintain correct sorted ordering.

      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Word>
      Parameters:
      other - the word to compare to
      Returns:
      negative if this word invalid input: '<' other, positive if >, zero if equal
